      "message": "this operates at byte level, which means it might incorrectly call cond() on a part of a rune.\n\ni think we should use range loop here. range loop over string automatically decodes runes as it runs.\n\nthis means, cond can be `func(rune) bool` which is related to my comment about reusing existing funcs. \n\n\n------------\n\nalso, this func looks very similar to https://godoc.org/strings#IndexFunc\ne.g. L243 could be\n\n  end :\u003d strings.IndexFunc(t.path[t.pos:], func(rune r) { return !unicode.IsDigit(r)})\n  if end !\u003d -1 { \n     ... \n  } else { \n     t.pos \u003d end\n  }\n\nup to you",
